#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code postfix ko infix me convert karne ke liye stack of strings use karta hai.

1. Expression ko left se right traverse karte hain.
2. Agar operand mile, to usse string bana ke stack me push kar do.
3. Agar operator mile, to stack se top ke 2 operands nikaalte hain:
   - pehla pop = second operand
   - doosra pop = first operand
4. Fir new infix expression banate hain:
   '(' + first + operator + second + ')'
5. Is naye expression ko dobara stack me push kar dete hain.
6. End me stack me jo final string bachegi wahi infix answer hoga.

Main idea:
Postfix me operator hamesha apne 2 operands ke baad aata hai,
isliye jaise hi operator milta hai, stack ke top ke 2 expressions ko combine kar dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public boolean isOperator(Character a){
        if((a == '+') || (a == '-') || (a == '*') || (a == '/')){
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public String postToInfix(String postExp) {
        // Your code goes here
        int n = postExp.length();
        int i = 0;
        ArrayDeque<String> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        while(i < n){
            char ch = postExp.charAt(i);

            if(isOperator(ch)){
                String second = stack.pop();
                String first = stack.pop();
                String temp = '(' + first + ch + second + ')';
                stack.push(temp);
            }
            //if operand
            else{
                stack.push(Character.toString(ch));
            }
            i++;
        }
        return stack.peek();
    }
}
